4. Architecture Principles

AP-001 Configuration Driven

Framework behavior shall be controlled through:

- Environment configuration
- Manifest configuration
- Artifact metadata

No artifact-specific logic shall be hardcoded into workflows.

---

AP-002 Runtime Host Selection

Execution hosts shall be supplied at runtime.

Environment definitions shall not contain static host mappings.

---

AP-003 Artifact Isolation

Each artifact shall execute in an isolated workspace.

Example:

/apps/regression/workspace/<run_id>/<artifact_name>

This prevents collisions during parallel execution.

---

AP-004 Reusability

Deployment, execution, validation, reporting, and notification capabilities shall be implemented using reusable Ansible roles.

