14. Reporting Framework

Objectives

Provide standardized execution visibility.

---

Artifact Report

Generated for every artifact.

Contains:

- Artifact name
- Status
- Start time
- End time
- Duration
- Validation status
- Failure details

---

Validation Report

Contains:

- Comparison result
- Difference summary
- Validation outcome

---

Execution Summary Report

Contains:

- Total artifacts
- Passed
- Failed
- Timed out
- Validation summary

---

Report Storage

/apps/regression/reports/<run_id>

---

AWX Publication

Reports shall be published as AWX job artifacts.

---

15. Notification Framework

Objectives

Provide execution visibility.

Supported notifications:

- Failure
- Completion
- Summary

---

Failure Notification

Triggered immediately when an artifact fails.

Contains:

- Artifact name
- Failure reason
- Job link

---

Completion Notification

Triggered when execution completes.

---

Summary Notification

Contains:

- Total executed
- Passed
- Failed
- Duration

---

16. Resume Framework

Objective

Recover from failed executions.

---

Resume Scope

Phase 1 supports:

Artifact-boundary resume only.

---

Checkpoint Structure

/apps/regression/checkpoints/<run_id>

---

Checkpoint Files

Example:

payment.completed
billing.failed
settlement.pending

---

Resume Rules

- Original host must be used
- Failed artifact becomes restart point
- Completed artifacts are skipped

---

